    "question_id" : 21276059,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For me, the issue was with type of columns. Query was fetching a text column. but jdbc was expecting an array of text.</p>\n<p>Started working once datatype was matched</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6503436,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 5033293,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/0tuBASCY.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Dawid Stankiewicz",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5033293/dawid-stankiewicz"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1760533152,
    "creation_date" : 1760533152,
    "answer_id" : 79791195,
    "question_id" : 21276059,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If anyone looking for this error in 2025+ then probably you're using vector type with JPA (maybe for embedding). I had this issue due to incorrect type in my entity for a vector column:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>    @Column(name = &quot;embedding&quot;, columnDefinition = &quot;vector(384)&quot;)\n    private float[] embedding;\n</code></pre>\n<p>It displayed <code>'Basic' attribute type should not be 'float[]'</code> error, which I unfortunately ignored.</p>\n<p>The solution is to add <code>hibernate-vector</code> dependency to the POM:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>        &lt;dependency&gt;\n            &lt;groupId&gt;org.hibernate.orm&lt;/groupId&gt;\n            &lt;artifactId&gt;hibernate-vector&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n            &lt;version&gt;6.6.26.Final&lt;/version&gt;\n        &lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>and following annotations for your vector column:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>    @Column(name = &quot;embedding&quot;, columnDefinition = &quot;vector&quot;)\n    @JdbcTypeCode(SqlTypes.VECTOR)\n    @Array(length = 384) // adjust to your vector length\n    private float[] embedding;\n</code></pre>\n<p>It was a kind of tricky error, because I got <code>org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: No results were returned by the query</code> during the second <code>save()</code> of my other entity (which had nested relation with entity having this <code>embedding</code>  column).</p>\n"
  } ],
